thread.title: Ellie Goulding redeems herself for AFL grand final with 'Activewear' parody clip
thread.title_full: Ellie Goulding redeems herself for AFL grand final with 'Activewear' parody clip

author: Ebony Bowden
title: Ellie Goulding redeems herself for AFL grand final with 'Activewear' parody clip
text:
Ellie Goulding plays herself in the new 'Activewear' parody sequel about our lycra obsession. 
Ellie Goulding: I wanted to give my all for Oz AFL Grand Final fail: Did Goulding lip sync? British singer Ellie Goulding has left a parting gift for her Australian fans after a horror performance at the AFL grand final earlier this month.
The 28-year-old Love Me Like You Do  singer had to defend herself against claims of lip syncing after a technician at the game accidentally broadcasted her pre-recorded vocals as she stood awkwardly on stage.
Goulding tweeting 5 Seconds of Summer in her activewear. 
But despite enduring a Meat Loaf-worthy grilling by the public, the singer made time while in Sydney to secretly record a parody video with Australian comedy trio Skit Box.
Advertisement The all-female comedy group shot to fame on YouTube last month with their 'Activewear' parody video making fun of our obsession with wearing lycra at all times.
The clip has notched up 2.5 million views in just two weeks and a line of parody t-shirts is already in the works.
Clearly a fan of the video, Goulding appears as herself in the sequel released this week which shows her doing everyday superstar things in her activewear.
The Nike ambassador is unsuprisingly clad in Nike as she jokes about tweeting Australian band 5 Seconds of Summer and firing her publicist in her activewear.
